channel.title: System can find Path specified
channel.description:
ok so i know this is a EV problum but i can figure out what im doing wrong
Heres what the run.bat has when you edit it
[code]@echo off title InsidiaX "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.7.0.\bin\java.exe" -Xmx1000m -cp bin;deps/poi.jar;deps/mysql.jar;deps/mina.jar;deps/slf4j.jar;deps/slf4j-nop.jar;deps/jython.jar;log4j-1.2.15.jar; server.Server pause[/code]
And heres what i have in my Classpath and Path
CLASSPATH: CLASSPATH=C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.7.0\bin;%CLASSPATH%;
PATH: C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.7.0\bin;
and their the same in both user variables and system variables.
I have look this up in google and did what they said to do and it didnt work.

item.title: System can find Path specified
item.dc:creator: @tyb97 tyb97
item.description:
@tyb97 wrote:

[quote=“demps2k9, post:16, topic:413346”]If your using windows 7, use this run code:

@echo off
title InsidiaX
"C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.7.0\bin\java.exe" -Xmx1000m -cp bin;deps/poi.jar;deps/mysql.jar;deps/mina.jar;deps/slf4j.jar;deps/slf4j-nop.jar;deps/jython.jar;log4j-1.2.15.jar; server.Server
pause

Also make sure you have set your enviroment variables as it required me to do so to make it work on my windows 7 laptop.

Classpath = CLASSPATH=C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.7.0\bin;%CLASSPATH%;
Path = C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.7.0\bin

There is no need for a ; with the Path.[/quote]
Also, if you set up your JDK to be installed in a different location, compensate for that by editing the codes in everything to be right…
